<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB01586</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT INSTITUTIONALIZING THE ALTERNATIVE LEARNING SYSTEM IN THE BASIC EDUCATION FOR OUT-OF-SCHOOL CHILDREN, YOUTH AND ADULTS, PERSONS WITH DISABILITIES, INDIGENOUS PEOPLES, AND OTHER MARGINALIZED SECTORS OF SOCIETY, AND APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to provide the out-of-school children, youth and adults, persons with disabilities, indigenous people, and other marginalized sectors of society with equally opportunities to improve their knowledge, technical and vocational efficiency, and other skills through systematic and flexible alternative basic education program outside of the formal school system.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Alternative Learning System Act of the Philippines.”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ROMUALDEZ, YEDDA MARIE K., ROMUALDEZ, FERDINAND MARTIN G.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-08</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Nieto (000 2019-09-25)</td><td>2. Lopez (M.L.) (000 2019-09-25)</td><tr><td>3. Suansing (H.) (000 2019-11-04)</td><td>4. Olivarez (000 2019-11-05)</td><tr><td>5. Lara (000 2019-11-06)</td><td>6. Fariñas (R.C.) (000 2019-11-19)</td><tr><td>7. Dalipe (000 2020-02-17)</td><td>8. Villarica (000 2020-02-19)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB06910</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON BASIC EDUCATION AND CULTURE ON 2019-07-24</td></tr></table>